    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ireland and Israel: Critical Difference; Absent Leadership</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Norman Mann letter says that settlement between Northern Ireland's secular political leaders demonstrates bankruptcy of Catholic and Protestant religious leaders</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The settlement between Northern Ireland's Roman Catholics and Protestants by secular political leaders demonstrates the bankruptcy of the religious leaders of these faiths (front page, April 11). The religious leadership of both faiths found that there was more diversity in their political life than unanimity in Christian belief. This conflict is another example that religious communities foster conflict and do little to heal rifts.</p>
        <p>NORMAN MANN  San Diego, April 11, 1998</p>
      </block>
